    "Dr. Peter S. Ruckman": "In the latter reference, the phony \u201chigh priest\u201d of Zechariah 11:15\u201317 is reigning on earth, but he is overthrown (Rev. 19:19\u201320) and has to pass the miter on to the \u201cSon of David `[char_David_Rut_4]`.\u201d The miter is a sort of \u201cwrap-around turban,\u201d and this explains why the Holy Spirit led the translators of the King James Bible to substitute \u201cdiadem\u201d for the same word in Ezekiel: the Antichrist has usurped not only the office of Priest ( as Saul ), but of KING ( as Saul ). (This should teach any novice a great lesson in understanding the Bible. The lesson is learned many times over by those who read the series of Bible Believer\u2019s Commentaries. It is simply that there is a supernatural hand on the \u201cinconsistencies\u201d of the AV text which cannot even be found in the consistencies of the Twentieth Century \u201cBibles\u201d\u2014any and all of them, by any group of translators of any profession.) Aaron `[char_Aaron_Exo_6]`\u2019s sons do not have the miter (for the head) or the breastplate (for the heart) or the onyx stones (for the shoulders of Aaron `[char_Aaron_Exo_6]`). Even though their identification with him is tremendous (note \u201cAaron `[char_Aaron_Exo_6]` and his sons\u201d \u201429:4, 9, 10, 15, 19, 28, 32), it is never complete, for the Lord Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ was the \u201conly begotten\u201d Son of God. Other sons are \u201cbegotten\u201d after they have been born once (1 Cor. 4:15; Phile. 10; 1 John `[char_John_Ref]` 5:1, 18). Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ was \u201cbegotten\u201d the first time He was born. Observe further how there is no \u201canointing\u201d (vs. 41) until the priests have \u201cput on Christ,\u201d in typology! On the front of the miter was a plate of pure gold, and engraven on it was \u201cHOLINESS TO THE LORD\u201d (vs. 36). It was tied to the turban by means of a blue lace, exactly as the breastplate was tied around the chest of the priest in\nverse\n26. In the latter reference, the phony \u201chigh [v_Zec_11_15] priest\u201d of Zechariah 11:15\u201317 is reigning on earth, but he [v_Rev_19_19] is overthrown (Rev. 19:19\u201320) and has to pass the miter on to the \u201cSon of David `[char_David_Rut_4]`.\u201d The `[group_Word_Luk_1]` miter is a sort of \u201cwrap-around turban,\u201d and this explains why the Holy Spirit led the translators of the King James Bible to substitute \u201cdiadem\u201d for the same word in Ezekiel: the Antichrist has usurped not only the office of Priest (as Saul), but of KING (as Saul). (This should teach any novice a great lesson in understanding the Bible. The `[group_Word_Luk_1]` lesson is learned many times over by those who read the series of Bible Believer\u2019s Commentaries. It is simply that there is a supernatural hand on the \u201cinconsistencies\u201d of the AV text which cannot even be found in the consistencies of the Twentieth Century \u201cBibles\u201d\u2014any and all of them, by any group of translators of any profession.) Aaron `[char_Aaron_Exo_6]`\u2019s sons do not have the miter (for the head) or the breastplate (for the heart) or the onyx stones (for the shoulders of Aaron `[char_Aaron_Exo_6]`). Even though their identification with him is tremendous (note \u201cAaron `[char_Aaron_Exo_6]` and his sons\u201d\u201429:4, 9, 10, 15, 19, 28, 32), it is never complete, for the Lord Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ was the \u201conly begotten\u201d Son of God. Other sons are \u201cbegotten\u201d after they have been born once (1 Cor. 4:15; Phile. 10; 1 John `[char_John_Ref]` 5:1, 18). Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ was \u201cbegotten\u201d the first time He was born. Observe further how there is no \u201canointing\u201d (vs. 41) until the priests have \u201cput on Christ,\u201d in typology! On the front of the miter was a plate of pure gold, and engraven on it was \u201cHOLINESS TO THE LORD\u201d (vs. 36). It was tied to the turban by means of a blue lace, exactly as the breastplate was tied around the chest of the priest in\nverse",
    "Commentary Vol. 83": "All the souls that came with Jacob `[char_Jacob_Ref]` into Egypt, etc.] These are in parcels before mentioned, but here they are brought to a sum total; and by this phrase are excluded those that died before, as Er and Onan, and those that were in Egypt before, as Joseph `[char_Joseph_Ref]` and his two sons; and I should think also all that were born in Egypt afterwards, even while Jacob `[char_Jacob_Ref]` was living: those reckoned are only such, which came out of his loins: such as were his seed and offspring. This is observed for the sake of what follows, and to exclude them: 778 besides Jacob `[char_Jacob_Ref]`\u2019s sons\u2019 wives; these do not come into the account, because they did not spring from him: all the souls [were] threescore and six; thirty two of Leah\u2019s, leaving out Er and Onan, sixteen of Zilpah\u2019s, fourteen of Rachel\u2019s, and seven of Bilhah\u2019s, make sixty nine; take out of them Joseph `[char_Joseph_Ref]` and his two sons, who were in Egypt before, and you have the exact number of sixty six.\nVer."
